ng the best-fit $H_0$ by $1.6$ km/s/Mpc. However, the addition of\nintermediate-redshift data (the JLA supernova dataset and baryon acoustic\noscillation data) weakens the effectiveness of this model. Only $\\sim 0.5$\\% of\nthe dark matter decays bringing the $S_8$ tension back up to $\\sim 1.5 \\sigma$\nand the increase in the best-fit $H_0$ down to $0.4$ km/s/Mpc.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Feb 2019 17:01:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Feb 2019 09:37:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 21 Oct 2019 19:29:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-14"}
